WEBVTT

01:14.690 --> 01:16.712
Welcome Concord, glad you're here.

01:16.773 --> 01:21.518
Everyone who is watching online, everyone who is on all of our campuses, we're glad you're here.

01:21.919 --> 01:28.427
I invite you to open up your Bibles to John chapter 11, and we're going to get into the subject in just a moment of, do you believe this?

01:29.668 --> 01:41.042
This week was our daughter's birthday, our youngest is a girl, she turned 15, and you know, some, as parents always say, men, do you believe that she's already 15 years old?

01:41.378 --> 01:42.580
We're getting a learner's permit.

01:42.940 --> 01:47.187
Very soon as we can get time to get over there to the Department of Driver Services.

01:48.048 --> 01:51.193
But when she was born, we were living in New York.

01:51.954 --> 01:56.661
Her two older brothers had been early in their birth.

01:56.721 --> 02:01.088
So my wife pregnant two other times with our boys.

02:01.208 --> 02:04.393
And so our first son was born a month early.

02:04.513 --> 02:06.957
Our second son was born two weeks early.

02:07.457 --> 02:10.482
And so our daughter, we assumed, would be born early, but no.

02:10.914 --> 02:13.478
She took her own sweet time and she was born late.

02:14.980 --> 02:21.209
So on her due date, my wife did not give birth, but that night we went to bed.

02:22.591 --> 02:27.418
So about two in the morning, my wife woke me up and said, I think we need to go to the hospital.

02:28.280 --> 02:29.281
Just having contractions.

02:29.341 --> 02:35.250
And back in those days, this was even before texting was going on,

02:35.362 --> 02:38.887
Email was sort of the most common way to get the word out quickly.

02:38.907 --> 02:40.510
I mean, still obviously we use email today.

02:40.530 --> 02:48.141
But our church family had told us, listen, we want to be praying and we want to know when you guys are going to the hospital, that kind of thing.

02:48.201 --> 02:49.063
So email us.

02:49.523 --> 02:51.927
And so I sat down to the computer to email.

02:52.027 --> 02:54.130
So two in the morning, sitting down for an email.

02:54.831 --> 02:56.253
My in-laws were there.

02:56.273 --> 02:59.178
They were going to be there to help with the boys and get the hospital with us and those kind of things.

02:59.238 --> 03:04.786
And so getting closer to three o'clock, my A.M., my wife came and said,

03:04.962 --> 03:07.505
I think we need to go to the hospital now.

03:08.727 --> 03:11.090
And I said, do I thought we had plenty of time?

03:11.170 --> 03:17.638
Because the first time, you know, a few minutes ago, almost an hour ago, she seemed fine, but the contractions were coming more and more quickly.

03:17.998 --> 03:27.730
We're about a 20-minute drive through the mountains there to the hospital, a very good hospital, in a small town, next town to us.

03:27.842 --> 03:35.010
In New York, in those days, just like in Georgia now, you're not allowed to talk on your phone, you know, cell phone as you're driving.

03:35.390 --> 03:40.456
However, we were in an emergency situation really quick.

03:40.556 --> 03:41.237
I realized this.

03:41.537 --> 03:51.769
On the way to the hospital, my wife's contractions were getting closer and closer, and I was really afraid I was gonna have to give birth in the car on the way to the hospital.

03:52.329 --> 03:53.451
Trying to figure out this is gonna happen.

03:53.891 --> 03:56.434
So I called the hospital and I said, we are on the way,

03:56.738 --> 03:58.840
My wife's in labor, be ready."

03:58.860 --> 03:59.922
And they're like, oh, yes, sir.

03:59.962 --> 04:03.826
And once you get to the hospital, just come down to labor and delivery and we'll take care of it.

04:03.866 --> 04:05.128
I'm like, no, no, you don't understand.

04:05.468 --> 04:08.171
We may not make it to the labor and delivery room.

04:08.912 --> 04:11.255
And so they met us at the door with a wheelchair.

04:12.316 --> 04:15.139
Roll us right down to the labor and delivery room.

04:15.640 --> 04:19.965
And my wife, it was 3.09 when we arrived at the hospital.

04:20.025 --> 04:24.210
My wife pushed one time and...

04:24.578 --> 04:26.100
There was a lot of screaming.

04:26.380 --> 04:27.302
I mean, a lot.

04:27.863 --> 04:29.505
It was really, really loud.

04:30.446 --> 04:33.691
So loud that it woke up the family next door.

04:33.751 --> 04:46.388
The poor little wife there, the mom to be, was, she was sleeping because they were getting ready the next morning to induce and she was gonna get birth to her first child.

04:46.949 --> 04:50.674
And so she was trying to get one good night's sleep

04:50.786 --> 04:54.691
before she was going to give birth, and she didn't know what labor was going to be.

04:55.151 --> 05:00.458
And all of a sudden, she's awakened in the middle of the night to my wife screaming at the top of her lungs.

05:01.499 --> 05:07.366
And after my wife screamed at one time, she turned to the nurse and said, can I get some pain medicine?

05:08.227 --> 05:11.491
And the nurse looked at her and said, honey, it is way too late for that.

05:12.592 --> 05:17.178
Because with our boys, the first son, not only was, it was a little crazy.

05:17.198 --> 05:20.562
He was a month early, but when we got to the hospital with him, it took

05:20.674 --> 05:26.042
12 hours for him to be born, you know, from all the contractions and everything with our second son.

05:26.442 --> 05:29.927
He was two weeks early, but it took eight hours for him to be born.

05:30.368 --> 05:33.132
And so my wife and I, we just assumed it'd be the same way.

05:33.172 --> 05:34.854
So again, our daughter completely different.

05:35.155 --> 05:39.281
She's a day late and now she's coming really fast.

05:39.861 --> 05:40.863
We got there at 309.

05:41.604 --> 05:42.946
She was born at 327.

05:43.026 --> 05:45.970
So we only had 18 minutes to spare.

05:46.338 --> 05:49.826
So I wasn't kidding when I said we almost had a baby in the car.

05:50.347 --> 05:53.413
So my wife is a real woman.

05:53.434 --> 05:55.458
She has natural childbirth, that kind of thing.

05:55.498 --> 05:57.081
So if you ever wondered about that.

05:57.603 --> 05:58.905
But that's our daughter.

05:58.986 --> 06:00.790
That's how she entered into the world.

06:01.311 --> 06:03.295
And she's an amazing young lady.

06:03.997 --> 06:06.482
On her birthday Friday, turned 15.

06:06.946 --> 06:11.776
She woke up early in the morning, not at 327, but still early.

06:12.176 --> 06:21.174
And we left at the house at 530 so she could get to school at 545 to help lead worship for her FCA group that meets on Friday morning.

06:21.194 --> 06:22.357
Fellowship of Christian Athletes.

06:22.677 --> 06:23.840
She helps lead worship there.

06:24.421 --> 06:27.026
And just an amazing young lady that loves the Lord.

06:27.138 --> 06:35.209
But we're gonna get to some things that maybe connect that story to our message today about delays and things like that and some impossible stuff going on.

06:35.569 --> 06:40.576
But I wanna talk to you just the setting of this story really quick in John chapter 11.

06:41.918 --> 06:45.763
Because as we think about Concord, we think about the people all around us.

06:45.803 --> 06:49.388
And we think about what is it for us to be a disciple of Jesus.

06:49.468 --> 06:53.554
And we've talked about that we are people who worship God.

06:54.178 --> 07:02.051
people who reach out to others with the good news of Jesus, people who grow in our own faith, and people who serve inside the church and outside.

07:02.932 --> 07:08.762
We have to ask the question, do we really believe that Jesus can do anything?

07:10.324 --> 07:11.406
Anything that he wants to do.

07:11.466 --> 07:19.259
You know, you heard in the story this morning, one of the videos that we watched about Ashley and man how God has changed your life.

07:20.220 --> 07:21.362
Do you really believe?

07:21.666 --> 07:24.250
that Jesus continues to change lives today?

07:24.311 --> 07:31.202
Is there any situation, any habit that Jesus can't help someone to overcome?

07:32.024 --> 07:38.475
Is there any sin that just is a strong moment in people's lives that God can't set them free from?

07:38.555 --> 07:40.338
Is there anybody so lost?

07:40.898 --> 07:42.060
that they never be saved?

07:42.080 --> 07:44.964
Is there any marriage in crisis that God can't restore?

07:45.345 --> 07:48.730
Is there any financial trouble that God can't meet that need?

07:48.770 --> 07:54.038
Is there any health crisis that God can't give you the grace and the strength to be your healer?

07:55.220 --> 07:56.763
Do you really believe this?

07:57.223 --> 08:07.679
And most importantly, do you really believe that the greatest need people have is saving faith in Jesus Christ.

08:08.160 --> 08:09.362
Do you really believe that?

08:10.050 --> 08:11.191
Do you really believe that?

08:12.193 --> 08:14.736
Let's look at John, chapter 11, verse 25.

08:14.776 --> 08:17.098
Will you stand with me, please, for the reading of God's Word?

08:19.061 --> 08:21.784
The Bible says we're gonna pick up right in the middle of the story.

08:21.864 --> 08:26.390
Jesus said to her, I am the resurrection and the life.

08:27.231 --> 08:31.996
The one who believes in me, even if he dies, will live.

08:32.036 --> 08:36.722
Everyone who lives and believes in me will never die.

08:37.924 --> 08:39.986
Do you believe this?

08:40.258 --> 08:40.979
Let's pray together.

08:44.003 --> 08:47.147
Our Heavenly Father, we are grateful for Your Word.

08:47.968 --> 08:48.729
It is true.

08:49.830 --> 08:53.876
We're grateful for Your Holy Spirit who brings us into all truth.

08:54.617 --> 08:57.360
Jesus, You are the way, the truth, and the life.

08:59.423 --> 09:04.369
And in this text, we see You are the resurrection and the life.

09:05.170 --> 09:08.114
You bring the dead back to life.

09:08.418 --> 09:10.680
You bring dead things back to life.

09:11.341 --> 09:20.529
And Jesus, we pray that through this text this morning, this scripture, the God you would teach us about situations and about things that we look at.

09:21.070 --> 09:28.997
And Lord Jesus, you would help us to see these truths that you want to teach us that we would not just be here's of the word, but we would do what it says.

09:29.858 --> 09:32.220
I pray, Father, for the lost that today they'll be saved.

09:33.321 --> 09:38.386
I pray for every believer that they would truly believe and they would trust in you.

09:38.786 --> 09:44.814
And they would take steps of obedience in what you're calling them to do next in the situations that you lead them to.

09:45.435 --> 09:46.096
Father, we love you.

09:46.116 --> 09:48.279
Again, now teach us through your word.

09:48.339 --> 09:49.981
In Jesus' name we pray, amen.

09:51.403 --> 09:54.827
John chapter 11, Jesus is with his disciples.

09:56.029 --> 10:01.236
And is it a place that's a little bit of ways from where Mary and Martha and Lazarus live?

10:02.217 --> 10:05.682
Word gets to him that his friend Lazarus is sick.

10:06.690 --> 10:12.236
Jesus in many times of the gospel, when he hears news like that, immediately begins to go.

10:12.276 --> 10:19.124
Sometimes he goes and then he speaks words of healing on the way the person's healed.

10:19.705 --> 10:22.348
Sometimes Jesus goes and gets there and brings healing.

10:23.409 --> 10:26.032
Jesus in John chapter 11 does something unusual.

10:26.752 --> 10:31.698
When he hears the news that Lazarus is sick, he just stays where he's at.

10:32.450 --> 10:33.851
His disciples don't understand.

10:33.911 --> 10:41.118
I mean, they think maybe it's because he's afraid if he goes too close to Jerusalem that he's going to be arrested or they're afraid of that.

10:41.639 --> 10:42.059
It's kind of things.

10:42.079 --> 10:45.622
They're not sure why he's staying, but he chooses to stay.

10:45.662 --> 10:48.966
There's six things real quickly.

10:48.986 --> 10:55.212
I want to show you in this passage because this passage says that Jesus is the resurrection in the life.

10:56.853 --> 11:02.098
And if you believe in him, even if you physically die,

11:02.722 --> 11:08.630
You will live, and everyone who lives and believes in him will never spiritually die.

11:09.191 --> 11:12.495
And then he asks this question, do you believe this?

11:13.457 --> 11:14.518
It's a huge question.

11:15.279 --> 11:18.523
It's a question of, do you really believe the Bible?

11:18.563 --> 11:20.746
That's the question we're asking.

11:21.127 --> 11:23.390
Do you really believe in Jesus?

11:24.151 --> 11:26.494
Do you really believe that truth about him?

11:27.095 --> 11:28.717
Do you really believe this?

11:29.879 --> 11:32.242
Because if you do, it changes everything.

11:33.154 --> 11:33.855
Everything.

11:34.595 --> 11:36.577
And we're gonna see six things that would change this morning.

11:36.697 --> 11:37.438
Number one is this.

11:38.759 --> 11:44.585
If you really believe this, it will change how you view delays.

11:45.766 --> 11:47.888
It'll change how you view delays.

11:49.189 --> 12:00.000
In verse 17, it says, when Jesus arrived, he found that Lazarus had already been in the tomb for days.

12:01.041 --> 12:02.482
Remember, Jesus had heard the

12:02.626 --> 12:04.648
News of his friend Lazarus was sick.

12:04.748 --> 12:05.930
Jesus stayed there.

12:06.390 --> 12:10.955
And then by the time he gets there, Lazarus has died and been in the tomb for days.

12:11.295 --> 12:17.222
In other words, there was this delay between when Jesus heard the news and when he responded.

12:18.103 --> 12:25.411
My question to you is, has there ever been a time when you informed God of something and then it took him a while to respond?

12:26.432 --> 12:32.018
In other words, have there ever been a time when you prayed for something and there was a delay?

12:32.674 --> 12:36.059
And you wondered, does God even care?

12:37.020 --> 12:38.081
Does he hear me?

12:38.622 --> 12:40.044
Does he know what's going on?

12:41.546 --> 12:45.211
Jesus on this day was going to bring Lazarus back from the dead.

12:45.592 --> 12:48.796
Spoiler alert, if you didn't know that's where we're going, that's where we're going in this story.

12:50.178 --> 12:56.868
Jesus in this delay showed that he had something deeper to teach about himself.

12:57.609 --> 13:01.554
The disciples already knew that he was the healer.

13:02.402 --> 13:04.966
He had healed people many times.

13:05.647 --> 13:14.260
They didn't know what he was about to show them on this day, about him being able to do what even the Jewish people that day would have said is impossible.

13:14.740 --> 13:29.202
See, the number four in terms of the four days really actually matters in this story because for the Jewish mindset of that day, they believed that if you passed away and then you were put into some kind of a tomb that

13:29.442 --> 13:39.475
They believe that your spirit sort of hung around for three days or maybe and and then you could come back to life maybe Kind of thing but after four days.

13:39.515 --> 13:57.458
They're like no that person is dead and gone So this number four in Lazarus means that not only is dead He's very dead and there is no way that Jesus could do anything And so when he Jesus gets there he's been in the tomb four days But the delay was on purpose

13:58.306 --> 14:11.560
So has it ever occurred to you that when you pray about something that God may delay on purpose, the delays have meaning, it will change the delays.

14:11.940 --> 14:20.228
Maybe God is gonna show you that He is always gonna provide exactly what is needed right on time.

14:21.550 --> 14:22.110
Did you hear that?

14:22.611 --> 14:25.714
God is gonna provide exactly what is needed in your life

14:25.794 --> 14:27.175
right on time.

14:27.516 --> 14:31.299
So don't let a delay wreck your faith.

14:31.519 --> 14:34.762
Don't let a delay cause you to question.

14:35.103 --> 14:43.391
Continue to seek the Lord, continue to trust in Him, continue to believe in Him and in His Word, in His ways, even when there's a delay.

14:43.811 --> 14:55.442
So if you believe, if you truly believe that Jesus is a resurrection of life and He can do the impossible, then it will change how you see delays because you will see that God's time is always perfect.

14:56.290 --> 15:02.337
Number two, not only will it change how you view delays, number two, it will reframe your discussions.

15:03.098 --> 15:04.740
It will reframe your discussions.

15:05.160 --> 15:15.712
Verse 18, and following Bethany was near Jerusalem, less than two miles away, and many of the Jews had come to Mary and Martha to comfort them about their brother.

15:16.673 --> 15:24.402
So as soon as Martha heard that Jesus was coming, she went to meet him, but Mary remained seated in the house.

15:25.090 --> 15:29.434
Then Martha said to Jesus, Lord, if you've been here, my brother wouldn't have died.

15:30.475 --> 15:34.799
For yet even now, I know that whatever you ask from God, God will give you.

15:35.680 --> 15:37.802
Your brother will rise again, Jesus told her.

15:38.823 --> 15:43.988
Martha said to him, I know that he will rise again in the resurrection at the last day.

15:44.869 --> 15:50.594
Jesus said to her, I am the resurrection of the life, the one who believes in me even if he dies will live.

15:51.134 --> 15:53.637
Everyone who lives and believes in me will never die.

15:54.137 --> 15:54.898
Do you?

15:55.650 --> 15:57.512
Martha, do you believe this?

15:57.632 --> 15:58.473
Do you believe her?

15:58.513 --> 15:58.873
Believe this.

15:59.494 --> 16:08.102
Verse 27, yes Lord, she told him, I believe that you're the Messiah, the Son of God who has come into the world.

16:10.384 --> 16:11.666
It will change your discussions.

16:12.186 --> 16:19.754
Martha, when Jesus arrived, ran there and said basically, if you would have been here, he would not have died.

16:21.235 --> 16:24.178
Jesus continued the conversation, says,

16:25.218 --> 16:27.320
that he is the resurrection in the life.

16:29.203 --> 16:32.366
And he says, before that, your brother will rise again.

16:32.386 --> 16:40.156
Martha thinks that Jesus is just talking about the future, that he will rise again at the great resurrection.

16:41.577 --> 16:43.780
There was a common thought in their culture at the time.

16:44.701 --> 16:52.370
Jesus is saying, no, not only can I, as he could arise in the future, Jesus is like, I can do it today.

16:53.634 --> 16:54.655
Here's the discussion.

16:54.675 --> 16:56.177
This is the change in the discussion.

16:56.878 --> 17:02.466
Some of you may believe, theoretically, that God may answer in the future.

17:03.467 --> 17:04.889
You might even say it this way.

17:05.871 --> 17:18.448
Yeah, my neighbor, my classmate, this person I go to college with, the person I work with, I believe they could get off drugs or they could get saved.

17:19.569 --> 17:22.994
Maybe one day God could change their life

17:24.546 --> 17:28.050
But what if the discussion is, what does God want to do today?

17:29.231 --> 17:38.381
Or you may say about yourself, yeah, I believe it could happen, theoretical, but do you believe that God can do it today?

17:39.702 --> 17:48.852
Because for some of you and all of our campuses online and in this room, some of you say, I need God to change me.

17:49.773 --> 17:51.154
The discussion is not about

17:51.970 --> 17:54.713
What could happen if discussion is today?

17:55.494 --> 17:56.354
Aim for believers?

17:56.975 --> 17:59.998
You say, yeah, I want my classmate.

18:00.018 --> 18:01.399
I want this person to go to school with.

18:01.600 --> 18:02.861
I want this neighbor.

18:02.901 --> 18:04.142
I want this coworker.

18:04.543 --> 18:08.707
I want them to get set free, to be healed, to believe in Jesus.

18:09.347 --> 18:11.289
Do you believe it could happen today?

18:11.650 --> 18:19.858
Because if Jesus is the resurrection of life, not only do we believe in the fact that what we said earlier, that we have a different view about delays,

18:20.386 --> 18:22.068
But it changes our discussions.

18:22.369 --> 18:25.133
It's not just theoretical about something that may happen.

18:25.533 --> 18:29.699
It is God, I believe Jesus can do this today.

18:29.979 --> 18:43.778
Because if I believe, if you believe that Jesus can save your neighbor today, and if you believe that Jesus is their only hope, it will bring motivation to you this week.

18:44.299 --> 18:45.281
It'll change how you pray.

18:46.342 --> 18:47.323
It'll change what you do.

18:47.844 --> 18:49.266
It'll change how you serve.

18:49.698 --> 18:52.081
It'll be like, I have got to invite them to church.

18:52.822 --> 18:54.503
I need to share my story with them.

18:55.084 --> 18:58.127
I need to serve them so that they will be drawn to Christ.

18:58.548 --> 19:01.391
Martha's, again, conversation with Jesus.

19:01.752 --> 19:03.874
If you had just been here, you could have done something.

19:04.134 --> 19:06.217
Jesus is like, no, I can do something.

19:06.797 --> 19:07.758
I can do something.

19:07.778 --> 19:08.779
Do you believe this?

19:10.301 --> 19:14.306
I know a lady who, she prayed for her husband for 28 years.

19:15.207 --> 19:18.130
Remember point number one, delays?

19:18.498 --> 19:19.960
She didn't stop believing.

19:22.122 --> 19:28.309
And she continued to give him opportunities, her husband, to come to church services.

19:28.349 --> 19:32.734
And it was, it took 28 years, but finally one day God saved him.

19:33.815 --> 19:34.876
Man, she believed.

19:35.657 --> 19:37.099
She believed, so what about you?

19:37.720 --> 19:40.503
Will you be faithful and believe in God?

19:41.264 --> 19:46.930
You know, I know people who are going through marriage crisis.

19:47.362 --> 19:56.676
And man, one of the, you know, spouse, the husband of the wife, man, they wonder from God or maybe turn her back on God and turn back on his word.

19:57.197 --> 20:04.067
Many times I've counseled the one who is, I mean, walking with the Lord is don't stop believing.

20:04.107 --> 20:06.131
Don't stop believing.

20:06.171 --> 20:09.175
Sometimes it feels like you have to have faith for both people.

20:10.036 --> 20:13.682
Don't stop believing that God in his word can do the impossible.

20:14.178 --> 20:16.482
You know, I don't know what's going on in your life.

20:16.562 --> 20:17.163
God does.

20:18.265 --> 20:28.664
But if you really believe that Jesus can bring a dead man back to life, and if you believe that Jesus himself brought himself back to life, it will change your discussions.

20:29.385 --> 20:33.853
It will change your discussions because you will say God can do the impossible.

20:34.434 --> 20:38.962
He may do it in the future, the delays, but he may do it today.

20:39.394 --> 20:40.656
I believe that he can do it today.

20:40.716 --> 20:41.938
It will change your discussions.

20:41.998 --> 20:44.421
It will reframe your discussions.

20:45.262 --> 20:50.510
Number three, now it will change how you view delays and reframe your discussions.

20:50.610 --> 20:53.334
Number three, it will eliminate your despair.

20:53.354 --> 20:56.398
I want you to notice that Martha is different all of a sudden.

20:56.678 --> 20:59.442
She believes in Jesus even when she goes to talk to her sister.

20:59.462 --> 21:00.083
Look at verse 28.

21:00.143 --> 21:07.794
It says, having said this, she went back and called her sister Mary saying in private, the teacher is here and he's calling for you.

21:08.194 --> 21:11.500
As soon as Mary heard this, she got up quickly and went to him.

21:12.682 --> 21:17.329
Jesus had not yet come into the village, but was still in the place where Martha had met him.

21:17.890 --> 21:23.320
The Jews who were with her in the house, consoling her, saw that Mary got up quickly and went out.

21:24.061 --> 21:27.927
They followed her, supposing that she was going to the tomb to cry there.

